# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STRICT WHITELIST .gitignore
# Track the public-facing code PLUS the dev/test material needed to build and
# verify it (fixtures, parity vectors, golden files). Everything else — specs,
# plans, reports, .github, .claude, node_modules — is ignored.
# NOTE: git tracking is intentionally BROADER than the npm tarball. The published
# package is narrowed further by package.json "files" (e.g. fixtures are tracked
# here so the self-test/golden suite runs on a clean checkout, but excluded from
# the tarball). git tracking ⊇ npm "files"; they are two separate whitelists.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1. Ignore everything by default…
*

# 2. …but still descend into directories so the allow-list can reach files.
!*/

# 3. Allow-list: repo-public root files.
!/.gitignore
!/package.json
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/CONTRIBUTING.md

# 4. Allow-list: distributed code trees (== package.json "files").
!/bin/**
!/hooks/**
!/rules/**
!/skills/**
# Native Rust scanner crate — source of a runtime binary. Build artifacts
# (target/) are re-ignored by tools/leakscan/.gitignore. Whole-crate tracking.
!/tools/**
# Native Rust engine crates — source of the runtime binary. Build artifacts
# (target/) re-ignored by each crate's .gitignore. Whole-crate tracking.
!/crates/**

# 5. Re-ignore genuine BUILD ARTIFACTS inside those trees (not test fixtures —
#    those are source-of-truth for the self-test/golden suite and ARE tracked,
#    even though package.json "files" excludes them from the npm tarball).
# Native engine binary is a BUILD ARTIFACT (cargo build --release → target/),
# resolved at runtime by bin/slopgate. Never track it; per-platform packaging
# of this binary is the deferred npm-distribution work.
bin/slopgate-rs
.worktrees/

# scratch / demo workspaces
tmp/
